        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2. Berinda hoerwegi sp. nov. (A–E = holotype, ♂, MHNG; F–G = paratype, ♂ from Kermanshah Provinve, MHNG; H–L = paratype, ♀ from Ilam Province, MHNG). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B–E. Palp, ventral, retrolateral and retroventral views. F. Apical portion of bulb. G. Tibial apophysis, retrolateral view. H, J–K. Epigyne, ventral view. I. Epigyne, dorsal view.L. Same, with schematic course of internal duct system.Abbreviation:Ah = anterior hood. Scale bars:A = 1 mm; B–C = 0.2 mm; F–G, K–L = 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4906011/files/figure.png" .

